293→        <p data-i18n="blog.prep.s1_label1"><strong>Early Warning Systems:</strong></p>
294→        <ul>
295→          <li data-i18n="blog.prep.s1_li1">Sign up for <strong>local emergency alerts</strong> through your city/county emergency management office. Most jurisdictions offer text/email alerts for civil disturbances.<sup><a href="#fn1" id="fnref1" class="fn-ref">[1]</a></sup></li>
296→          <li data-i18n="blog.prep.s1_li2">Monitor <strong>verified local news</strong> and police scanner apps (Broadcastify) for real-time updates.</li>
297→          <li data-i18n="blog.prep.s1_li3">Use <strong>social media monitoring</strong> tools like TweetDeck to follow local hashtags and official accounts, but verify information before acting.<sup><a href="#fn1" id="fnref1b" class="fn-ref">[1]</a></sup></li>
298→        </ul>
